The paper deals with the problem of post-hoc calibration of machine learning classifiers, which is a common issue in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on uncertainty calibration in deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
